INSERT INTO `quranic_verses_quizquestion` VALUES (1,'Which chapter of the Quran is known as \"The Opening\"?','Surah Al-Baqarah','Surah Al-Fatiha','Surah Al-Ikhlas','Surah Al-An\'am','Surah Al-Fatiha',1,'Sura Al-Fatiha (“The Opening”) is the first chapter of the Quran containing 7 verses. Its verses are a prayer for God\'s guidance and stress the Lordship and Mercy of God (Allah in Arabic).'),(2,'Which Surah of the Quran is named after a spider?','Surah Al-Ankabut','Surah Al-Nahl','Surah Al-Rum','Surah Al-A\'raf','Surah Al-Ankabut',1,'The sura has been named Ankabut because of ayat no.41 which talks of the fragility of the false gods, comparing them to the web of a spider.'),(3,'Which chapter of the Quran is often referred to as \"The Cow\"?','Surah Al-Baqarah','Surah Al-An\'am','Surah Al-Nisa','Surah Al-Fatiha','Surah Al-Baqarah',1,'Why the name AL-BAQARAH? AL-BAQARAH (the Cow) has been so named from the story of the Cow occurring in this Surah (vv. 67-73). It has not, however, been used as a title to indicate the subject of the Surah.'),(4,'Which Surah of the Quran is known for its emphasis on patience and steadfastness?','Surah Al-Baqarah','Surah Al-Anfal','Surah Yusuf','Surah Al-Asr','Surah Al-Asr',1,'The last verse of Surah Al-Asr translates as \'save those who have faith and do righteous deeds, and counsel each other to hold on to truth and counsel each other to be steadfast.\''),(5,'In which Surah of the Quran is the story of the Queen of Sheba mentioned?','Surah Al-Nisa','Surah Al-Mujadila','Surah An-Naml','Surah Al-Furqan','Surah An-Naml',1,'The account of the meeting of Suleiman (as) (Solomon in the Torah and Bible) and Bilqis, the Queen of Sheba, can be read in the 27th surah, Surah an-Naml (The Ant), ayahs 15 through 44.'),(6,'Which chapter of the Quran is the shortest in terms of verses?','Surah Al-Kawthar','Surah Al-Ikhlas','Surah Al-Falaq','Surah Al-Baqarah','Surah Al-Kawthar',1,'Surah al-Kawthar is the shortest chapter in The Quran, consisting of just three Ayahs or verses – even shorter than Surah al-Asr.'),(7,'In which Surah of the Quran is the story of Prophet Adam and his creation mentioned?','Surah Al-Anfal','Surah Al-Baqarah','Surah Al-Isra','Surah Sad','Surah Al-Baqarah',1,'Prophet Adam has been mentioned in The Quran in several  Verses, among them Verses from 30 to 38 of Surah Al-Baqarah (2nd Surah  of Quran) and verses from 11 to 25 of Surah Al-A\'raaf (7th Surah of  Quran).'),(8,'Which Surah of the Quran is named after the story of the night journey of the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him)?','Surah Al-Muzzammil','Surah Al-Isra','Surah Al-Furqan','Surah Al-A\'raf','Surah Al-Isra',1,'Within the Quran, chapter (surah) 17 al-Isra, was named after the Isra\', and the first verse contains a brief description. There is also some information in a later verse, and some scholars say a verse in surah an-Najm also holds information on the Isra and Miʿraj.'),(9,'Which chapter of the Quran is often referred to as \"The Light\"?','Surah Al-Nur','Surah Al-Baqarah','Surah Al-Mulk','Surah Al-A\'raf','Surah Al-Nur',1,'Surah Al-Nur , the 24th chapter in the Holy Quran often referred to as the light. In fact, the 35th verse of this chapter is known as \'Verse of light\', and translates as \'Allah is the light of the heavens and the earth; a likeness of His light is as a niche in which is a lamp, the lamp is in a glass, (and) the glass is as it were a brightly shining star, lit from a blessed olive-tree, neither eastern nor western, the oil whereof almost gives light though fire touch it not – light upon light\'.'),(11,'Which fruit is mentioned in the Quran as one of the blessings of Paradise?','Apples','Bananas','Oranges','Pears','Bananas',2,'The banana is considered a fruit of paradise, and although today it is seen as a common fruit, it holds numerous health benefits that can help maintain a balanced body. It is mentioned in the Quran here:  “And the People of the right? How (lucky) are the People of the Right! (They will be) amid lote-trees with no thorns, and the trees of TalH, (banana, or a fragrant tree) having layers one upon the other, and a shade, spread all over…” (56:27-30)'),(12,'Which fruit was mentioned three times in the Quran?','Dates','Bananas','Pomegranate','Mangoes','Pomegranate',2,'A favorite fruit used in juices, syrups, and savory dishes, the pomegranate is a huge part of many Muslim cultures today. Appearing in the Quran three times, the pomegranate is often mentioned in relation to Heaven and Allah’s gift to humankind:  “And besides these two [gardens in Heaven], there are two other gardens (for the second category of the God-fearing)…So, which of the bounties of your Lord will you deny? – both (gardens are) dark green! So, which of the bounties of your Lord will you d'),(13,'What is the Quran\'s guidance regarding dealing with orphans?','Neglect them','Exploit their vulnerability','Treat them kindly and justly','Isolate them from society','Treat them kindly and justly',3,NULL),(14,'How does the Quran instruct believers to respond to those who insult or abuse them?','Seek revenge','Respond with kindness and forgiveness','Retaliate with equal harm','Ignore the insults','Respond with kindness and forgiveness',3,NULL),(15,'In the Quran, which flower is mentioned as a symbol of beauty and grace, often associated with Paradise?','Rose','Lily','Tulip','Lotus','Lotus',4,'One notable flower mentioned in the Quran is the lotus, known as \"sudra\" in Arabic. The lotus symbolized purity and grace and is referenced in the Quran to illustrate the beauty of Allah\'s creation. The lotus is described as a flower that blooms in paradise, representing the divine beauty and tranquility that awaits righteous believers. Its presence in the Quran serves to remind Muslims of the eternal rewards and blessings that await those who strive for righteousness.'),(16,'What natural substance is mentioned in the Quran for its healing properties and is widely recognized for its medicinal benefits today?','Olive oil','Frankincense','Honey','Saffron','Honey',5,'Islamic books state that the prophet Mohammed (peace be upon him) referred to three methods in curing an illness: “a drink of honey, a scratch of hijamah and cautery.”'),(17,'What phrase is repeated at the beginning of most chapters (Surahs) in the Quran and signifies the start of a chapter?','\"In the name of Allah, the Most Gracious, the Most Merciful\"','\"All praise is due to Allah, the Lord of the Worlds\"','\"Say, \'He is Allah, [Who is] One\'\"','\"And We have certainly created man...\"','\"In the name of Allah, the Most Gracious, the Most Merciful\"',6,NULL),(18,'What Quranic value emphasizes honesty, truthfulness, and trustworthiness in one\'s actions and dealings with others?','Injustice','Rude','Honesty','Humility','Honesty',7,NULL),(19,'According to the Quran, what role are humans assigned on Earth, which involves stewardship and responsible care for the planet?','Dominance and control','Ownership and exploitation','Stewardship and responsibility','Passive observation','Stewardship and responsibility',8,'The Almighty created human beings mainly to perform two vital roles. Firstly, to be His Khalifa meaning vicegerent or steward; and secondly, to be His servant (Quran 2:30).'),(20,'What is considered the primary and most significant miracle in Islam, as mentioned in the Quran?','The mountains','The splitting of the moon','The Quran itself','Sky','The Quran itself',9,'Prophet Muhammad’s Quran is the biggest miracle Although the miracles listed above are extraordinary, none stack up to the greatest miracle of the Prophet ﷺ, The Holy Quran. No Muslim can disagree that the final revelation from the final Messenger ﷺ  is the undisputed greatest of his miracles. The miracle of the Holy Quran can be proven from multiple perspectives from its historical precision, its linguistic perfection to the many prophecies it accurately foretold. It is a book that was revealed'),(21,'According to the Quran, which prophet received the Tawrat (Torah) as a divine revelation?','Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him)','Prophet Abraham (Ibrahim in Arabic)','Prophet Moses (Musa in Arabic)','Prophet Jesus (Isa in Arabic)','Prophet Moses (Musa in Arabic)',10,NULL),(22,'n the Quran, what term is commonly used to describe food and actions that are permissible and lawful for Muslims to consume and engage in?','Sunnah','Halal','Haram','Zakat','Halal',11,'Halal foods are foods that Muslims are allowed to eat or drink under Islamic Law that specifies what foods are allowed and how that food must be prepared (halal means proper and permitted).'),(23,'How many times a day are Muslims required to perform the obligatory prayer (Salat) according to the Quran?','Two times','Three times','Five times','Seven times','Five times',12,NULL);
